---
import DocsLayout from '@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout
  title="shuttle dev"
  description="Full reference for the dev command: up, down, restart, logs, and status subcommands."
  section="commands"
>
  <p>
    <code>shuttle dev</code> manages a local Docker Compose development environment that mirrors
    your production <code>shuttle.yml</code> configuration. Running <code>shuttle dev</code>
    without a subcommand is equivalent to <code>shuttle dev up</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>shuttle dev up</h2>
  <p>Start (or restart) the development environment.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle dev up
shuttle dev      # same as above
</code></pre>
  <p>What this does:</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Checks for mkcert SSL certificates in <code>.shuttle/certs/</code> — generates them if mkcert is installed and they don't exist yet.</li>
    <li>Generates <code>.shuttle/Caddyfile.dev</code> with reverse proxy entries for your app services.</li>
    <li>Generates <code>docker-compose.dev.yml</code> in the project root with all services, accessories, and the Caddy container.</li>
    <li>Runs <code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml up -d --build</code>.</li>
    <li>Prints the HTTPS URL(s) for your app.</li>
  </ol>

  <h2>shuttle dev down</h2>
  <p>Stop all development containers.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle dev down
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Runs <code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml down</code>. Named volumes are preserved
    — your database data survives a <code>down</code> and <code>up</code> cycle. Use
    <code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml down -v</code> to remove volumes too.
  </p>

  <h2>shuttle dev restart</h2>
  <p>Stop then start the development environment.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle dev restart
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Equivalent to <code>shuttle dev down &amp;&amp; shuttle dev up</code>. Useful after changing
    your <code>shuttle.yml</code> to regenerate the compose file and Caddyfile.
  </p>

  <h2>shuttle dev logs</h2>
  <p>Stream logs from all development containers.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle dev logs              # follow mode (default)
shuttle dev logs --no-follow  # print current logs and exit
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Wraps <code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml logs [-f]</code>. All containers
    (app services, Caddy, accessories) output to the same stream with container name prefixes.
  </p>

  <h2>shuttle dev status</h2>
  <p>Show the running status of all development containers.</p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">shuttle dev status
</code></pre>
  <p>
    Runs <code>docker compose -f docker-compose.dev.yml ps</code>. Shows container names,
    images, commands, and status (Up/Exit):
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">NAME                    IMAGE               STATUS          PORTS
myapp-web-1             myapp-web           Up 5 minutes    3000/tcp
myapp-caddy-1           caddy:2-alpine      Up 5 minutes    0.0.0.0:80-&gt;80/tcp, 0.0.0.0:443-&gt;443/tcp
myapp-postgres-1        postgres:16         Up 5 minutes    5432/tcp
myapp-redis-1           redis:7-alpine      Up 5 minutes    6379/tcp
</code></pre>

  <h2>Generated files</h2>
  <p>
    Both files are regenerated on each <code>shuttle dev up</code> call:
  </p>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>File</th>
        <th>Location</th>
        <th>Purpose</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>Caddyfile.dev</code></td>
        <td><code>.shuttle/Caddyfile.dev</code></td>
        <td>Caddy reverse proxy config for local dev</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>docker-compose.dev.yml</code></td>
        <td>Project root</td>
        <td>Compose file with all services and accessories</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>
    These can be safely added to <code>.gitignore</code>:
  </p>
  <pre><code class="language-bash">docker-compose.dev.yml
.shuttle/Caddyfile.dev
.shuttle/certs/
</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
